44. DSA Nonce Recovery from Repeated Nonce

Recovering the private key when the same nonce k is reused

Step 1
Given:
Multiple signed messages (each with trailing space)

Public key (y):
2d026f4bf30195ede3a088da85e398ef869611d0f68f07...

Same domain parameters as previous challenge (p, q, g)

Step 2
Observation:
Some messages share the same nonce k

Effect:
- same k → same r
- signatures with identical r are candidates

Step 3
Given two signatures with same k:
Message 1:
m1, r, s1
Message 2:
m2, r, s2

Step 4
> Recover k

k = \frac{m_1 - m_2}{s_1 - s_2} \bmod q

- m1, m2 = hash values of messages
- subtraction is done mod q
- modular inverse required

Step 5

> Compute Private Key x
x = \frac{s k - H(m)}{r} \bmod q

- use either (m1, s1) or (m2, s2)
- both produce same x

Step 6

> Process
1. Parse all messages and signatures
2. Find pairs with identical r
3. Compute k using formula
4. Compute x using recovered k
5. Verify correctness

Step 7
> Result
Recovered private key x

    SHA-1 fingerprint:
    ca8f6f7c66fa362d40760d135b763eb8527d3d52


CODE (Java)

import java.math.BigInteger;
import java.util.*;

public class DSANonceRecovery {
static BigInteger q = new BigInteger("f4f47f05794b256174bba6e9b396a7707e563c5b", 16);  

public static void main(String[] args) {  

    // Example structure (populate from file)  
    class Sig {  
        BigInteger r, s, m;  
        Sig(BigInteger r, BigInteger s, BigInteger m) {  
            this.r = r; this.s = s; this.m = m;  
        }  
    }  

    List<Sig> sigs = new ArrayList<>();  

    //load actual data   

    for (int i = 0; i < sigs.size(); i++) {  
        for (int j = i + 1; j < sigs.size(); j++) {  

            Sig a = sigs.get(i);  
            Sig b = sigs.get(j);  

            if (a.r.equals(b.r)) {  

                BigInteger k = (a.m.subtract(b.m))  
                        .multiply(a.s.subtract(b.s).modInverse(q))  
                        .mod(q);  

                BigInteger x = (a.s.multiply(k).subtract(a.m))  
                        .multiply(a.r.modInverse(q))  
                        .mod(q);  

                System.out.println("Private key:");  
                System.out.println(x.toString(16));  
            }  
        }  
    }  
}  
}

Notes:

> same r
  * indicates reused nonce k
> (m1 - m2)
  * difference of message hashes
> (s1 - s2).modInverse(q)
  * modular inverse for division
> nested loop
  * checks all signature pairs
> a.r.equals(b.r)
  * detects reused k
